# Web Rules (React + Vite)

Template for React projects using Vite.

## Routing

- React Router v6 for navigation
- Lazy load route components with `React.lazy()`
- Route guards in `routes/guards/`

## Component Structure

```
src/
├── components/
│   ├── ui/           # Reusable UI primitives
│   └── [feature]/    # Feature-specific components
├── hooks/            # Custom hooks
├── pages/            # Route components
├── services/         # API services
└── stores/           # State management
```

## State Management

| Type | Solution |
|------|----------|
| Server State | TanStack Query |
| Client State | Zustand |
| Form State | React Hook Form |
| URL State | React Router |

## API Integration

```typescript
// services/api.ts
export const apiClient = {
  get: <T>(url: string) => fetch(url).then(r => r.json() as T),
  post: <T>(url: string, data: unknown) => 
    fetch(url, { method: 'POST', body: JSON.stringify(data) }).then(r => r.json() as T),
};

// hooks/useUsers.ts
export const useUsers = () => useQuery({ queryKey: ['users'], queryFn: userService.list });
```

## Component Patterns

```typescript
// ✅ Good: Function component with typed props
interface ButtonProps {
  variant: 'primary' | 'secondary';
  onClick: () => void;
  children: React.ReactNode;
}

export function Button({ variant, onClick, children }: ButtonProps) {
  return <button className={styles[variant]} onClick={onClick}>{children}</button>;
}
```

